  "@type": "Article",
  "dateModified": "2026-03-03",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-03",
  "description": "Wage labor is the social relation in which a person sells their capacity to work (labor-power) to an employer in exchange for a wage. It is not simply \u0026ldquo;working for money\u0026rdquo; but a specific arrangement in which the worker, lacking independent access to the means of production (land, tools, materials), must sell their labor-power as a commodity on the market. The employer buys this commodity and directs its use, keeping what it produces.\n",
  "name": "Wage Labor",
